2. cs.SI - The study of complex systems is also a key area of research in systems and information science. The approach of partitioning an object into its irreducible parts and counting the steps by which the object can be reassembled from those parts is a common technique in systems science. 
3. cs.LG - The use of graph-based models to represent objects and their formation history is a common technique in machine learning. The concept of pathway complexity can also be seen as a measure of the complexity of a system, which is a key area of research in machine learning. 
4. cs.DS - The concept of pathway assembly involves analyzing the structure of complex systems, which is a key area of research in data structures. The use of graph-based models to represent objects and their formation history is also a common technique in data structures. 
5. cs.CC - The study of complex systems and their behavior is a key area of research in computational complexity. The concept of pathway complexity can also be seen as a measure of the computational complexity of a system.
